The paper deals with complexity classification of constraint satisfaction problems (CSPs) on finite domains, which is a topic that falls under computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also introduces a new tractable case for CSPs, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper uses techniques from graph theory and combinatorics, which are relevant to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
